{
  "stem": "11611.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I mean, nothing we were doing was gonna make the Germans fonder of the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were kind of a vestige of the war and out of date.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the bank cases were proposed to be reduced from two banks to one, with one defendant from the bank.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Taylor first said, is there anything to these bank cases?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Are they worth a damn?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Rawlings and Goldenberg said, yup, there was some merit to them, but they were tough cases and might not be able to be proven.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "By this time, the atmosphere in the courts was not all that favorable either.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a bunch of state court judges, some of whom were-- not many, but at least a couple of them were damn near pro-German.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These were US judges?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yeah, these were all state court judges, generally supreme courts of the various states.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were invited by the Department of Justice of the War Department to go in Nuremberg and some of them decided to do it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So these, Goldenberg and [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Ragland ?] had some reservations about whether the cases would be successful, but I didn't have any reservations.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know any better.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, yeah, I think the case is good.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Taylor said, you want to work on it?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said, yeah, I want to keep working on it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Rawlings, [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ragland, ?] and Herb Goldenberg were switched to the Krupp Trial team, and they really ran that team in good part successfully.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I then became the sole prosecutor in the bank case, which was Karl Rasche.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Among his other functions, he was an SS colonel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was pretty good.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Dresden Bank had an old saying which translated, 'Who goes before the first German tank?",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
